Reply to Nurse Ratchet or who ever you really are:<br>
I must admit that your list of student involvements is quite long, but what is the relavancy here?  PS,your 486 is ill, it posted three times as you probably have seen. Of course, I'll stick to my power Mac.<br><br>
I unloaded, or vented on you, not out of my need to unload personal stress, but to try and get you to see how pompous you sounded. (like I used too). How out of touch with the average grunts on this site you were. I don't think you have figured that out yet. I hope you do.  Are you also know as Lou Cohen?  If so why not admit it. If not, then you two share a very similiar type of writing and phraseology.  It was very honest of you to at least tell us you will lurk around for awhile.  (I win the bet about that).<br><br>
I don't want to waste space here about me, and what I realize is my &quot;pre&quot; and &quot;post&quot; doc thinking.  Check my dialoges with Arthur V or Tom Dier on Site #48.  <br><br>
I think the real issue between you and the majority of posters (not protestors) on this site is that you just &quot;don't get it&quot;.  To say you &quot;protested with my vote&quot; is the biggest piece of nonthinking crap ever voiced.  If you can't figure out why guys who friends died in their arms knee deep in rice paddies, or guys who fled to canada, or Nurses who bravely and silently tended the wounded and maimed, or even the protestors, who risked 5 years in Federal Prison to stand their position, your comment is an insensitive, inaccurate, and insulting position. Think about it.<br><br>
Let me try one more example: You don't think you work in an Ivory Tower and you list all these &quot;sensitivity groups&quot; and support groups that you are involved in.  That is so academic of you.  That is NOT, I repeat, NOT the real world.<br>
A typical day in one of my offices resulted in two involuntary hospitalizations (5150's) which ment kicking and screaming, cops, a broken window and two schizophrenic young kids getting locked up against their will. 3 Homeless people needing to get into our drug rehab program, but had no money, 5 newly busted for drugs youngsters coming up with dirty drug tests and being told bye bye, you just chose to go to jail, 4 couples divorcing, 1 teacher having dreams of machine gunning his students, a dozen or so angry lawyers screaming for this or that, reports late, reports not done, Judges yelling, etc. etc.  All that is just a day in the life, and I am not bragging or venting.  But PLEASE, do not compare life on the campus to life on the street. That is so &quot;liberal&quot; of you as to be hysterical.  <br><br>
By the way Nurse, I too have a teaching credential,  High School and College, political science or psych.  I tried it out, but found it was too UN-real for me.  I know where you come from, the problem is you don't.   You think that the &quot;stress&quot; you experience is the pinnacle of stress, and you don't seem to get it that it isn't.  Oh my god, you teach 4 classes in 4 different class rooms.  That isn't stress, that's a breeze.  I bet that even takes you a week, not just one day, right?  That is exactly the point I am trying to get you to see.  Using that as someform of &quot;see I am as good as the rest of you guys&quot; makes you look like a simpleton. Stop trying to be an equal, just be a learner.  Perhaps you have more to read and less to say. I know that's hard when you have had a captive audience for most of your life, i.e. the classroom.  Next you will be telling me that giving a grade to a student is the same &quot;stress&quot; as starting an I.V.in a bouncing elevator or ducking bullets in a fire fight.<br><br>
It took me alot of soul searching to be honest and realize that I was carrying alot of old material internally about viet nam and veterans.  I rethought my innards, and surprise, my thinking and writing changed.  Can you do the<br>
same?  <br><br>
Are we to think you a world traveler because you went to Rosarito Beach?  That's about as Mexican as Tiajuana, 25 miles to the North.  Why even mention it?  (I guess teachers can't afford laptops huh?)  The question I ask is are you (1) the type of tourist who goes to that tourist trap of a town called Rosarito Beach and thinks this is &quot;real&quot; Mexico and comes back a world traveler and expert on Mexico and all things Mexican, or (2) someone who goes to Rosarito Beach, eats seafood, drinks too many Margarita's, and comes home no better and no wiser, and just a bit fatter.  Glad you had your spring break, teach, perhaps now you can see thinks from a new point of view.<br><br>
Oh, Nurse R, last thing. I like you. As a fellow acamadician, and there are only two of us here (that I know of), I feel the need, the honor, to educate the educator, as many other's here (who I am sure you think of as uneducated) have so taught me.  I got to stop. You are becoming my thesis.  If you want to pursue this one-to-one, use my email and let's not take our &quot;academic&quot; discourse our on the &quot;street&quot; of this site.<br><br>
